(3, 9, 2, 'Stop Worrying and Start Enjoying: Why Mobile Phone Insurance is a Must-Have for Every Smartphone Owner', 'stop-worrying-and-start-enjoying-why-mobile-phone-insurance-is-a-must-have-for-every-smartphone-owner', 'Super Admin', '2023-02-23-63f73e5d65cab.jpeg', 'Written By Anika Tabassum\r\n\r\nPicture this- You&#39;re on a once-in-a-lifetime vacation, exploring a new city and soaking in the sights and sounds. You reach for your phone to snap a photo, but your heart sinks as you realize it&#39;s not there. You&#39;ve lost your lifeline to the world back home, and with it, all of your precious memories, contacts, and information. This scenario may seem like a nightmare, but unfortunately, it&#39;s a reality that many smartphone owners have faced. That&#39;s why mobile phone insurance is not just a luxury, but a necessity for anyone who values their phone and the peace of mind that comes with it. In this article, we&#39;ll explore the importance of mobile insurance and provide you with everything you need to know to make an informed decision about protecting your mobile investment.\r\n\r\nMobile phones have become an integral part of our daily lives. From communication to entertainment, we rely on our phones for a variety of tasks. However, with the increasing use of smartphones, the risk of accidental damage, theft, or loss has also risen.\r\n\r\n\r\n	According to a recent survey, 33% of smartphone users in Bangladesh reported experiencing some kind of damage to their phone in the past year. (Source: Statista)\r\n	Theft of mobile phones is a growing problem in Bangladesh, with an estimated 4,000 phones stolen every day. (Source: The Daily Star)\r\n	The average cost of repairing a damaged smartphone screen in Bangladesh is around Tk 7,000 (USD 82), while the cost of a new phone can range from Tk 15,000 (USD 176) to Tk 50,000 (USD 586) or more, depending on the model. (Source: The Daily Star)\r\n\r\n\r\nDespite the risks and potential costs, a recent survey found that very few smartphone users in Bangladesh even know about mobile phone insurance. These statistics highlight the importance of mobile phone insurance for smartphone users in Bangladesh, as it can provide protection and peace of mind in the event of damage, theft, or loss.\r\n\r\nMobile insurance is a type of insurance policy that covers the cost of repairing or replacing a damaged, stolen, or lost phone. It offers peace of mind knowing that your mobile investment is protected.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHere are some key things to keep in mind when considering mobile insurance:\r\n\r\n\r\n	Coverage: Before purchasing mobile insurance, it&#39;s important to understand what type of coverage is offered. Some insurance policies may only cover accidental damage, while others may also include protection against theft or loss.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n	Cost: The cost of mobile insurance varies depending on the coverage offered, the phone&#39;s make and model, and the insurance company. It is important to compare the cost of insurance with the cost of repairing or replacing the phone, and to choose a policy that offers the best value for your investment.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n	Deductible: Most insurance policies require the payment of a deductible, which is the amount that you will pay out of pocket in the event of a claim. Consider the size of the deductible when comparing insurance policies.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n	Claims process: Make sure to understand the claims process before purchasing mobile insurance. How do you file a claim? How long does it take to process? What is the process for replacing a lost or stolen phone? These are important questions to ask when considering mobile insurance.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n	Exclusions: It&#39;s important to understand what is not covered under the insurance policy. For example, some policies may exclude coverage for intentional damage, such as breaking the phone on purpose.\r\n\r\n\r\nIn today&#39;s world, where our smartphones are with us at all times and have become integral to our daily lives, the need for mobile phone insurance is more important than ever. Accidents happen, and the cost of repairing or replacing a damaged, lost, or stolen phone can be significant. But with the right coverage in place, you can have peace of mind knowing that your mobile investment is protected. That&rsquo;s where InstaSure comes into play, with different packages to choose from.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nBefore purchasing mobile insurance, it&#39;s important to consider factors such as coverage, cost, deductible, claims process, and exclusions. Take the time to research and compare policies to find the best option for your needs and budget. With the right coverage, you can stop worrying and start enjoying your phone, knowing that you&#39;re prepared for whatever may happen.\r\n\r\nSo don&#39;t wait until it&#39;s too late. Invest in mobile phone insurance today and enjoy the benefits of a protected and worry-free mobile experience.', '<h3>Written By Anika Tabassum</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Picture this- You&#39;re on a once-in-a-lifetime vacation, exploring a new city and soaking in the sights and sounds. You reach for your phone to snap a photo, but your heart sinks as you realize it&#39;s not there. You&#39;ve lost your lifeline to the world back home, and with it, all of your precious memories, contacts, and information. This scenario may seem like a nightmare, but unfortunately, it&#39;s a reality that many smartphone owners have faced. That&#39;s why mobile phone insurance is not just a luxury, but a necessity for anyone who values their phone and the peace of mind that comes with it. In this article, we&#39;ll explore the importance of mobile insurance and provide you with everything you need to know to make an informed decision about protecting your mobile investment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mobile phones have become an integral part of our daily lives. From communication to entertainment, we rely on our phones for a variety of tasks. However, with the increasing use of smartphones, the risk of accidental damage, theft, or loss has also risen.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>According to a recent survey, 33% of smartphone users in Bangladesh reported experiencing some kind of damage to their phone in the past year. (Source: Statista)</li>\r\n	<li>Theft of mobile phones is a growing problem in Bangladesh, with an estimated 4,000 phones stolen every day. (Source: The Daily Star)</li>\r\n	<li>The average cost of repairing a damaged smartphone screen in Bangladesh is around Tk 7,000 (USD 82), while the cost of a new phone can range from Tk 15,000 (USD 176) to Tk 50,000 (USD 586) or more, depending on the model. (Source: The Daily Star)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Despite the risks and potential costs, a recent survey found that very few smartphone users in Bangladesh even know about mobile phone insurance. These statistics highlight the importance of mobile phone insurance for smartphone users in Bangladesh, as it can provide protection and peace of mind in the event of damage, theft, or loss.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mobile insurance is a type of insurance policy that covers the cost of repairing or replacing a damaged, stolen, or lost phone. <strong>It offers peace of mind knowing that your mobile investment is protected.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here are some key things to keep in mind when considering mobile insurance:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Coverage: Before purchasing mobile insurance, it&#39;s important to understand what type of coverage is offered. Some insurance policies may only cover accidental damage, while others may also include protection against theft or loss.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Cost: The cost of mobile insurance varies depending on the coverage offered, the phone&#39;s make and model, and the insurance company. It is important to compare the cost of insurance with the cost of repairing or replacing the phone, and to choose a policy that offers the best value for your investment.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Deductible: Most insurance policies require the payment of a deductible, which is the amount that you will pay out of pocket in the event of a claim. Consider the size of the deductible when comparing insurance policies.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Claims process: Make sure to understand the claims process before purchasing mobile insurance. How do you file a claim? How long does it take to process? What is the process for replacing a lost or stolen phone? These are important questions to ask when considering mobile insurance.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Exclusions: It&#39;s important to understand what is not covered under the insurance policy. For example, some policies may exclude coverage for intentional damage, such as breaking the phone on purpose.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>In today&#39;s world, where our smartphones are with us at all times and have become integral to our daily lives, the need for mobile phone insurance is more important than ever. Accidents happen, and the cost of repairing or replacing a damaged, lost, or stolen phone can be significant. But with the right coverage in place, you can have peace of mind knowing that your mobile investment is protected. That&rsquo;s where <strong>InstaSure</strong> comes into play, with different packages to choose from.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before purchasing mobile insurance, it&#39;s important to consider factors such as coverage, cost, deductible, claims process, and exclusions. Take the time to research and compare policies to find the best option for your needs and budget. With the right coverage, you can stop worrying and start enjoying your phone, knowing that you&#39;re prepared for whatever may happen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So don&#39;t wait until it&#39;s too late. Invest in mobile phone insurance today and enjoy the benefits of a protected and worry-free mobile experience.</p>', 'blog', 1, '2023-02-23 16:22:21', '2023-02-27 10:54:45'),
(4, 9, 2, 'The Protection You Need, Insuring Against the Unexpected', 'the-protection-you-need-insuring-against-the-unexpected', 'Super Admin', '2023-02-25-63f9eab15cad2.jpeg', 'Written By Anika Tabassum\r\n\r\nUnderstanding Mobile Phone Theft Insurance and Damage Coverage Options\r\n\r\nHave you ever experienced the feeling of dread when you realize you&#39;ve lost or damaged your phone? That sinking feeling in your stomach, the frustration of being disconnected from the world, and the worry of the cost to replace or repair your device. It&#39;s an all too common scenario in today&#39;s world, as according to a study conducted by the Bangladesh Mobile Phone Business Association, around 1.5 million smartphones are lost or stolen in Bangladesh every year. In this blog post, we&#39;ll explore the differences between mobile phone theft insurance and damage protection plans, and why it&#39;s important to understand your options when it comes to insuring your phone.\r\n\r\nA report by The Daily Star found that the number of mobile phone thefts in Bangladesh has increased by 150% over the past three years, with Dhaka being the most common location for thefts. Mobile phone insurance typically covers the cost of repairing or replacing a damaged, lost, or stolen phone. This type of insurance is typically purchased separately from the phone itself (but at the same time of purchasing), and can cover accidental damage, theft, and other types of losses.\r\n\r\nThe cost of repairing a damaged smartphone in Bangladesh can range from BDT 1,000 to BDT 30,000, depending on the extent of the damage and the phone&#39;s make and model. The most common causes of smartphone damage in the country are drops, followed by liquid damage and scratches. Given the situation, it is a smart decision to get a damage protection plan for our devices. Damage protection plans are sometimes offered by manufacturers or retailers and provide limited coverage for accidental damage. This type of coverage may also cover repair or replacement costs, but is often limited in scope and duration. No matter the case, with InstaSure you can now insure your phone even if your manufacturer is not providing insurance.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMobile phone insurance and damage protection plans are two different types of insurance coverage for mobile phones. Here are some key differences between them:\r\n\r\n\r\n	Coverage: Mobile phone insurance provides more comprehensive coverage than damage protection plans. Mobile insurance policies cover accidental damage, theft, and loss, while damage protection plans may only cover accidental damage.\r\n	Cost: The cost of mobile phone insurance and damage protection plans can vary widely depending on the policy and the phone&#39;s make and model. Mobile phone insurance may typically cost more than a damage protection plan, which is often offered at the time of phone purchase.\r\n	Deductible: Mobile phone insurance policies often require the payment of a deductible, which is the amount that you will pay out of pocket in the event of a claim. Damage protection plans may also have a deductible, but this may be waived or reduced if the plan was purchased at the time of phone purchase.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\r\n	\r\n		\r\n			\r\n			Days since you bought the insurance\r\n			\r\n			\r\n			Discounted price\r\n			\r\n		\r\n		\r\n			\r\n			0-30 days\r\n			\r\n			\r\n			Not eligible for claim\r\n			\r\n		\r\n		\r\n			\r\n			31-90 days\r\n			\r\n			\r\n			90% of your insured money\r\n			\r\n		\r\n		\r\n			\r\n			91-180 days\r\n			\r\n			\r\n			80% of your insured money\r\n			\r\n		\r\n		\r\n			\r\n			181-270 days\r\n			\r\n			\r\n			70% of your insured money\r\n			\r\n		\r\n		\r\n			\r\n			271-365 days\r\n			\r\n			\r\n			60% of your insured money\r\n			\r\n		\r\n	\r\n\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\r\n	Claims process: The claims process for mobile phone theft insurance and damage protection plans can vary depending on your location and type of insurance you are trying to claim. To claim theft insurance, you may need a copy of FIR as a proof of your stolen device. On the other hand, a damage protection plan can be claimed only with the NID that was used at the time of buying the insurance. Make sure to understand the process for filing a claim and the expected turnaround time for repairs or replacement.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n	Exclusions: It&#39;s important to understand the exclusions for both mobile phone insurance and damage protection plans. Some policies may exclude coverage for intentional damage or loss, or for damage caused by certain types of events or conditions.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIn conclusion, mobile phone theft and damage can happen to anyone, at any time, and can result in significant financial loss. With the increasing prevalence of these incidents, it is essential to take steps to protect your phone and your investment. Both mobile phone insurance and damage protection plans can provide coverage for accidental damage, but mobile phone insurance offers more comprehensive coverage. Before purchasing either type of coverage, it is important to understand the coverage offered, the cost, the deductible, the claims process, and any exclusions. By taking the time to research and choose the right insurance or protection plan for your mobile phone, you can have peace of mind knowing that you are prepared for the unexpected. Don&#39;t wait until it&#39;s too late - always insure your phone with InstaSure and protect yourself from the unexpected.', '<h3>Written By Anika Tabassum</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Understanding Mobile Phone Theft Insurance and Damage Coverage Options</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have you ever experienced the feeling of dread when you realize you&#39;ve lost or damaged your phone? That sinking feeling in your stomach, the frustration of being disconnected from the world, and the worry of the cost to replace or repair your device. It&#39;s an all too common scenario in today&#39;s world, as according to a study conducted by the Bangladesh Mobile Phone Business Association, <strong>around 1.5 million smartphones are lost or stolen in Bangladesh every year</strong>. In this blog post, we&#39;ll explore the differences between mobile phone theft insurance and damage protection plans, and why it&#39;s important to understand your options when it comes to insuring your phone.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>A report by The Daily Star found that the number of mobile phone thefts in Bangladesh has increased by 150% over the past three years, with Dhaka being the most common location for thefts.</strong> Mobile phone insurance typically covers the cost of repairing or replacing a damaged, lost, or stolen phone. This type of insurance is typically purchased separately from the phone itself (but at the same time of purchasing), and can cover accidental damage, theft, and other types of losses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The cost of repairing a damaged smartphone in Bangladesh can range from BDT 1,000 to BDT 30,000, depending on the extent of the damage and the phone&#39;s make and model.</strong> The most common causes of smartphone damage in the country are drops, followed by liquid damage and scratches. Given the situation, it is a smart decision to get a damage protection plan for our devices. Damage protection plans are sometimes offered by manufacturers or retailers and provide limited coverage for accidental damage. This type of coverage may also cover repair or replacement costs, but is often limited in scope and duration. <strong>No matter the case, with InstaSure you can now insure your phone even if your manufacturer is not providing insurance.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mobile phone insurance and damage protection plans are two different types of insurance coverage for mobile phones. Here are some key differences between them:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Coverage: Mobile phone insurance provides more comprehensive coverage than damage protection plans. Mobile insurance policies cover accidental damage, theft, and loss, while damage protection plans may only cover accidental damage.</li>\r\n	<li>Cost: The cost of mobile phone insurance and damage protection plans can vary widely depending on the policy and the phone&#39;s make and model. Mobile phone insurance may typically cost more than a damage protection plan, which is often offered at the time of phone purchase.</li>\r\n	<li>Deductible: Mobile phone insurance policies often require the payment of a deductible, which is the amount that you will pay out of pocket in the event of a claim. Damage protection plans may also have a deductible, but this may be waived or reduced if the plan was purchased at the time of phone purchase.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:624px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Days since you bought the insurance</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Discounted price</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>0-30 days</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>Not eligible for claim</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>31-90 days</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>90% of your insured money</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>91-180 days</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>80% of your insured money</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>181-270 days</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>70% of your insured money</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>271-365 days</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p>60% of your insured money</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Claims process: The claims process for mobile phone theft insurance and damage protection plans can vary depending on your location and type of insurance you are trying to claim. <strong>To claim theft insurance, you may need a copy of FIR as a proof of your stolen device. On the other hand, a damage protection plan can be claimed only with the NID that was used at the time of buying the insurance.</strong> Make sure to understand the process for filing a claim and the expected turnaround time for repairs or replacement.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Exclusions: It&#39;s important to understand the exclusions for both mobile phone insurance and damage protection plans. Some policies may exclude coverage for intentional damage or loss, or for damage caused by certain types of events or conditions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nIn conclusion, mobile phone theft and damage <strong>can happen to anyone, at any time, and can result in significant financial loss</strong>. With the increasing prevalence of these incidents, it is essential to take steps to protect your phone and your investment. Both mobile phone insurance and damage protection plans can provide coverage for accidental damage, but mobile phone insurance offers more comprehensive coverage. Before purchasing either type of coverage, it is important to understand the coverage offered, the cost, the deductible, the claims process, and any exclusions. By taking the time to research and choose the right insurance or protection plan for your mobile phone, you can have peace of mind knowing that you are prepared for the unexpected.<strong> Don&#39;t wait until it&#39;s too late - always insure your phone with InstaSure</strong> and protect yourself from the unexpected.</p>', 'blog', 1, '2023-02-25 17:02:09', '2023-02-27 10:54:54'),
(5, 9, 3, 'Travel with Peace of Mind:  Why You Need Travel Insurance for Your Next Trip', 'travel-with-peace-of-mind-why-you-need-travel-insurance-for-your-next-trip', 'Super Admin', '2023-02-27-63fc372b87eac.jpeg', 'Written By Anika Tabassum\r\n\r\nAre you planning a road trip with friends, or a tour overseas? Whether it&#39;s for business or pleasure, travel can be an exciting adventure. But with all the unknowns that come with traveling, it&#39;s important to be prepared for any unexpected events that may arise. According to the World Health Organization (WHO), road traffic injuries are the leading cause of death for people aged 15-29 years, and the ninth leading cause of death for all age groups globally. Moreover, The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) reported that in 2022, there were over 917 million international travelers, and of those travelers, 60% had one or more travel-related illnesses. This is where travel insurance comes in. When you purchase travel insurance, you&#39;re not just protecting yourself from potential financial losses, you&#39;re also getting peace of mind.\r\n\r\nTraveling can be an exhilarating experience, but it also comes with its own set of risks. You never know when unforeseen circumstances can derail your trip, leaving you stranded or facing unexpected expenses. This is where travel insurance comes in, providing peace of mind and protection when you&#39;re away from home. In this blog post, we&#39;ll explore five key benefits of purchasing travel insurance from our company, and how they can help you stay prepared for any eventuality. Whether you&#39;re planning a relaxing beach holiday or an adventurous trek through the wilderness, our travel insurance has got you covered. So, let&#39;s dive in and discover why our insurance is a must-have for your next trip.\r\n\r\nNatural Death Benefit\r\n\r\nWhile we don&#39;t like to think about it, death is a reality of life. According to the World Health Organization (WHO), cardiovascular diseases alone were the leading cause of natural deaths worldwide in 2019, accounting for 17.9 million deaths. In the unfortunate event of a natural death during your travels, a travel insurance policy can provide financial assistance to your loved ones back home. This benefit ensures that the policy holder&#39;s family receives a lump sum amount in the event of the policy holder&#39;s death during the trip.\r\n\r\nAccidental Death Benefit\r\n\r\nAccidental Death Facts:\r\n\r\n\r\n	According to the World Health Organisation&#39;s latest World Health Ranking published in 2020, Bangladesh ranks 88th among 183 countries in road accident death rate. The death rate is 16.74 per 1 lakh, in a scripted answer, Obaidul Quader said.\r\n	According to the National Safety Council (NSC), in the United States, the number of preventable deaths from accidents increased by 2% from 2018 to 2019, with a total of 169,936 deaths.\r\n	In India, the number of deaths due to road accidents increased from 1,34,796 in 2018 to 1,51,113 in 2019, an increase of 11.6%, according to data from the Ministry of Road Transport and Highways.\r\n\r\n\r\nJust like with natural death, accidental death can also occur during your travels. If an accident causes your death, your travel insurance policy can provide financial assistance to your family. In case of the policy holder&#39;s accidental death during the trip, this benefit ensures that their family receives a substantial sum of money.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAccidental Hospitalization Benefit (As per Schedule)\r\n\r\nAccording to The Business Standard, road accident patients alone occupy 19% of beds in primary and secondary hospitals. They said people injured in road accidents are hospitalized for an average of six days, which costs a patient Tk 5,834 on average.\r\n\r\nAccidents can happen anywhere, and if you find yourself hospitalized due to an accidental injury during your travels, your travel insurance policy can help cover the medical costs. This benefit ensures that the policy holder&#39;s medical expenses are covered in case of an accidental hospitalization during the trip.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMedical Conditions (COVID-19)\r\n\r\nWith the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic, travel can be risky. As of February, 2023, there have been over 426 million confirmed cases of COVID-19 worldwide, according to the World Health Organization (WHO). Many countries have strict entry requirements, which may include proof of vaccination and negative test results. If you fall ill during your trip, a travel insurance policy can provide coverage for medical expenses related to COVID-19. This benefit ensures that the policy holder&#39;s COVID-19 related medical expenses are covered in case you catch COVID-19 during the trip.\r\n\r\nTelemedicine Service\r\n\r\nAccording to a study by the US National Library of Medicine, the risk of blood clots in the legs, also known as deep vein thrombosis (DVT), increases during long-distance travel, with the risk being highest for flights over 8 hours. In case of a medical emergency during your travels, you may not be able to access medical care right away. A travel insurance policy may offer telemedicine services, which allow you to consult with a doctor over the phone or through video chat. This benefit ensures that the policy holder can receive medical advice and guidance remotely 24/7.\r\n\r\nTravel insurance is an investment that can provide peace of mind and financial protection during your travels. With benefits such as natural and accidental death coverage, accidental hospitalization coverage, COVID-19 medical coverage, and telemedicine services, a travel insurance policy can ensure that you&#39;re prepared for the unexpected events that may occur during your trip. These benefits not only provide peace of mind but also ensure that you are protected during unforeseen circumstances while traveling. Don&#39;t let a mishap ruin your travel plans; instead, invest in our travel insurance policy and make the most out of your travel experience. So, pack your bags and set out on a journey with confidence knowing that insurance has got you covered every step of the way.', '<h3>Written By Anika Tabassum</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Are you planning a road trip with friends, or a tour overseas? Whether it&#39;s for business or pleasure, travel can be an exciting adventure. But with all the unknowns that come with traveling, it&#39;s important to be prepared for any unexpected events that may arise. According to the World Health Organization (WHO), road traffic injuries are the leading cause of death for people aged 15-29 years, and the ninth leading cause of death for all age groups globally. Moreover, The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) reported that in 2022, there were over 917 million international travelers, and of those travelers, 60% had one or more travel-related illnesses. This is where travel insurance comes in. When you purchase travel insurance, you&#39;re not just protecting yourself from potential financial losses, you&#39;re also getting peace of mind.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Traveling can be an exhilarating experience, but it also comes with its own set of risks. You never know when unforeseen circumstances can derail your trip, leaving you stranded or facing unexpected expenses. This is where travel insurance comes in, providing peace of mind and protection when you&#39;re away from home. In this blog post, we&#39;ll explore five key benefits of purchasing travel insurance from our company, and how they can help you stay prepared for any eventuality. Whether you&#39;re planning a relaxing beach holiday or an adventurous trek through the wilderness, our travel insurance has got you covered. So, let&#39;s dive in and discover why our insurance is a must-have for your next trip.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Natural Death Benefit</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>While we don&#39;t like to think about it, death is a reality of life. According to the World Health Organization (WHO), cardiovascular diseases alone were the leading cause of natural deaths worldwide in 2019, accounting for 17.9 million deaths. In the unfortunate event of a natural death during your travels, a travel insurance policy can provide financial assistance to your loved ones back home. This benefit ensures that the policy holder&#39;s family receives a lump sum amount in the event of the policy holder&#39;s death during the trip.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Accidental Death Benefit</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Accidental Death Facts:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>According to the World Health Organisation&#39;s latest World Health Ranking published in 2020, Bangladesh ranks 88th among 183 countries in road accident death rate. The death rate is 16.74 per 1 lakh, in a scripted answer, Obaidul Quader said.</li>\r\n	<li>According to the National Safety Council (NSC), in the United States, the number of preventable deaths from accidents increased by 2% from 2018 to 2019, with a total of 169,936 deaths.</li>\r\n	<li>In India, the number of deaths due to road accidents increased from 1,34,796 in 2018 to 1,51,113 in 2019, an increase of 11.6%, according to data from the Ministry of Road Transport and Highways.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Just like with natural death, accidental death can also occur during your travels. If an accident causes your death, your travel insurance policy can provide financial assistance to your family. In case of the policy holder&#39;s accidental death during the trip, this benefit ensures that their family receives a substantial sum of money.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Accidental Hospitalization Benefit (As per Schedule)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to The Business Standard, road accident patients alone occupy 19% of beds in primary and secondary hospitals. They said people injured in road accidents are hospitalized for an average of six days, which costs a patient Tk 5,834 on average.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Accidents can happen anywhere, and if you find yourself hospitalized due to an accidental injury during your travels, your travel insurance policy can help cover the medical costs. This benefit ensures that the policy holder&#39;s medical expenses are covered in case of an accidental hospitalization during the trip.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Medical Conditions (COVID-19)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>With the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic, travel can be risky. As of February, 2023, there have been over 426 million confirmed cases of COVID-19 worldwide, according to the World Health Organization (WHO). Many countries have strict entry requirements, which may include proof of vaccination and negative test results. If you fall ill during your trip, a travel insurance policy can provide coverage for medical expenses related to COVID-19. This benefit ensures that the policy holder&#39;s COVID-19 related medical expenses are covered in case you catch COVID-19 during the trip.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Telemedicine Service</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to a study by the US National Library of Medicine, the risk of blood clots in the legs, also known as deep vein thrombosis (DVT), increases during long-distance travel, with the risk being highest for flights over 8 hours. In case of a medical emergency during your travels, you may not be able to access medical care right away. A travel insurance policy may offer telemedicine services, which allow you to consult with a doctor over the phone or through video chat. This benefit ensures that the policy holder can receive medical advice and guidance remotely 24/7.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Travel insurance is an investment that can provide peace of mind and financial protection during your travels. With benefits such as natural and accidental death coverage, accidental hospitalization coverage, COVID-19 medical coverage, and telemedicine services, a travel insurance policy can ensure that you&#39;re prepared for the unexpected events that may occur during your trip. These benefits not only provide peace of mind but also ensure that you are protected during unforeseen circumstances while traveling. Don&#39;t let a mishap ruin your travel plans; instead, invest in our travel insurance policy and make the most out of your travel experience. So, pack your bags and set out on a journey with confidence knowing that insurance has got you covered every step of the way.</p>', 'blog', 1, '2023-02-27 10:52:59', '2023-02-27 10:54:19');
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`id`, `user_id`, `blog_category_id`, `title`, `slug`, `author`, `image`, `short_description`, `description`, `type`, `status`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(6, 9, 5, 'Increase Revenue and Customer Satisfaction with InstaSure: Unleashing the Power of Embedded Insurance', 'increase-revenue-and-customer-satisfaction-with-instasure-unleashing-the-power-of-embedded-insurance', 'Super Admin', '2023-03-11-640c414b9ef5e.jpeg', 'Written By Anika Tabassum\r\n\r\nAs a business owner, you are always looking for new ways to grow your business and increase your revenue. One way to do this is by offering embedded insurance to your customers. Whether you sell products or provide services, adding insurance to your offerings can provide a range of benefits for both you and your customers. In this blog post, we&#39;ll explore the advantages of embedded insurance and show you how it can help take your business to the next level, regardless of your size or industry.\r\n\r\nEmbedded insurance is a type of insurance that is integrated into another product or service that the consumer is already purchasing. This means that the insurance coverage is added on as a feature of the main product or service, and this extra added-on feature is increasing the value of your product or service. Because of that you are always one step ahead of your competitor. This is one of the main reasons why embedded insurance is becoming increasingly popular among businesses as they can leverage this feature to gain recurring customers. On the other hand, customers prefer this before they trust this customer-centric mindset adapted by the business. Also because it provides an easy way for customers to obtain coverage without having to go through a separate application process.\r\n\r\n\r\nEmbedded insurance would increase sales\r\n\r\nAccording to a recent report by FinTech Global, the global embedded insurance market is projected to grow to $3.4 billion by 2025. This growth is being driven by businesses looking for innovative ways to offer insurance as a value-add to their products and services, while also generating additional revenue streams.\r\n\r\nIn fact, a survey by Deloitte found that 84% of businesses believe that embedding insurance into their products and services would improve customer loyalty, while 72% of consumers would be willing to pay for insurance as part of a bundled product or service.\r\n\r\nWe found that gen z (18-24 yrs) and millennials (25-40 yrs) favor embedded digital insurance due to automated claims, immediate payouts and the fact that non-traditional risks are covered. And when asked if they would purchase this type of insurance, 64% of gen x (41-56 yrs) and 58% boomers (57-65 yrs) chose &#39;yes&#39;. Read more about it in this blog.\r\n\r\nCustomers spend more when offered protection\r\n\r\nA study shows that 60% of consumers prefer to buy protection from their favorite online retailer, and that 32% of customers would buy more items and spend more on them if they were offered protection at the checkout. In fact, consumers desire embedded insurance offered directly by their financial institutions - Read in detail.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, the use of embedded insurance is not limited to specific industries, even though it is more popular among electronics and automobiles. For example, a small furniture store could offer embedded insurance for their products, such as protection against accidental damage or stains. This could give customers peace of mind and potentially lead to repeat business. The store could also charge an additional fee for the insurance, generating extra revenue.\r\n\r\nOn a different note, a small variety store can benefit from embedded insurance by offering insurance on the products they sell. If the store sells electronic gadgets, they can offer insurance to customers who purchase those gadgets. This will provide peace of mind to customers and increase their confidence in purchasing from the store. The store can potentially increase their revenue and profitability as customers love the added protection. The store can also differentiate themselves from competitors by offering this added value to customers. Overall, embedded insurance can be a valuable tool for small businesses to provide additional protection and increase their revenue.\r\n\r\nMoreover, by partnering with a specialized embedded insurance provider like InstaSure, small businesses can offer a wider range of insurance options to their customers without having to take on the costs and administrative burdens of creating their own insurance products.\r\n\r\nBenefits of Including Embedded Insurance in Your Products or Services\r\n\r\n\r\n	Increased revenue through an additional revenue stream\r\n	Improved customer satisfaction by offering a complete solution\r\n	Competitive advantage over businesses that don&#39;t offer embedded insurance\r\n	Reduced administrative hassle for businesses and customers\r\n	Enhanced Customer Experience\r\n	Enriched Risk Management\r\n\r\n\r\nInstaSure and its customizable embedded insurance product\r\n\r\nInstaSure is a leading insurance provider that offers embedded insurance solutions to businesses of all sizes. Our customizable insurance product can be tailored to suit the unique needs of any business, whether they provide products or services. With InstaSure, businesses can unlock new opportunities and expand their customer base while providing a convenient and hassle-free insurance experience to their clients.\r\n\r\nInstaSure is committed to helping small and large businesses grow and thrive for the long term. Our customizable embedded insurance product allows businesses to provide added value to their customers while protecting their investments. By offering insurance alongside their products or services, they can improve customer satisfaction and loyalty, while also increasing revenue and staying competitive in their respective markets. With InstaSure, businesses can stay ahead of the game and ensure long-term success.\r\n\r\nConclusion\r\n\r\nTo sum up, embedded insurance is a simple and effective way for businesses of all sizes to increase revenue and provide value to their customers. By partnering with InstaSure, businesses can customize their insurance offerings to fit their unique products or services and unlock new opportunities for growth. Embedded insurance will provide peace of mind to customers and increase their confidence to purchase from the store again and again. So, the business can potentially gain customer loyalty and generate more revenue in the long run. That&rsquo;s what businesses should do, think about the long game, because after all not all businesses can stay in the game till the end, only those who think about the extended play and plan ahead.\r\n\r\nOur team is dedicated to helping businesses stay competitive in the market and thrive for the long term. Contact us today to learn more about how we can help you integrate embedded insurance into your business. Call +880 9606 25252', '<h3>Written By Anika Tabassum</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>As a business owner, you are always <strong>looking for new ways to grow your business and increase your revenue</strong>. One way to do this is by offering embedded insurance to your customers. Whether you sell products or provide services, adding insurance to your offerings can provide a range of benefits for both you and your customers. In this blog post, we&#39;ll explore the advantages of embedded insurance and show you how it can help take your business to the next level, <strong>regardless of your size or industry.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Embedded insurance is a type of insurance that is integrated into another product or service that the consumer is already purchasing. This means that the insurance coverage is added on as a feature of the main product or service, and <strong>this extra added-on feature is increasing the value of your product or service</strong>. Because of that you are always <strong>one step ahead of your competitor</strong>. This is one of the main reasons why embedded insurance is becoming increasingly popular among businesses as they can <strong>leverage this feature to gain recurring customers.</strong> On the other hand, customers prefer this before they trust this customer-centric mindset adapted by the business. Also because it provides an easy way for customers to obtain coverage without having to go through a separate application process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nEmbedded insurance would increase sales</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to a recent report by FinTech Global, the global embedded insurance market is projected to grow to $3.4 billion by 2025. This growth is being driven by businesses looking for innovative ways to offer insurance as a value-add to their products and services, while also <strong>generating additional revenue streams.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In fact, a survey by Deloitte found that 84% of businesses believe that embedding insurance into their products and services would improve customer loyalty, while <strong>72% of consumers would be willing to pay for insurance as part of a bundled product or service.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We found that gen z (18-24 yrs) and millennials (25-40 yrs) favor embedded digital insurance due to automated claims, immediate payouts and the fact that non-traditional risks are covered. And when asked if they would purchase this type of insurance, 64% of gen x (41-56 yrs) and 58% boomers (57-65 yrs) chose &#39;yes&#39;. Read more about it in this <a href=\"https://www.companjon.com/news/embedded-insurance-is-the-secret-weapon-for-business-growth/\">blog</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Customers spend more when offered protection</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://covergenius.com/retail-insurance-study/\">A study</a> shows that 60% of consumers prefer to buy protection from their favorite online retailer, and that 32% of customers would buy more items and spend more on them if they were offered protection at the checkout. In fact, consumers desire embedded insurance offered directly by their financial institutions - <a href=\"https://covergenius.com/embedded-insurance-global/\">Read in detail</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Furthermore, the use of <strong>embedded insurance is not limited to specific industries</strong>, even though it is more popular among electronics and automobiles. For example, a small furniture store could offer embedded insurance for their products, such as protection against accidental damage or stains. This could give customers peace of mind and potentially lead to repeat business. The store could also charge an additional fee for the insurance, generating extra revenue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On a different note, a small variety store can benefit from embedded insurance by offering insurance on the products they sell. If the store sells electronic gadgets, they can offer insurance to customers who purchase those gadgets. This will provide peace of mind to customers and increase their confidence in purchasing from the store. The store can potentially increase their revenue and profitability as customers love the added protection. The store can also differentiate themselves from competitors by offering this added value to customers. Overall, embedded insurance can be a <strong>valuable tool for small businesses to provide additional protection and increase their revenue</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Moreover, by partnering with a specialized embedded insurance provider like InstaSure, small businesses can offer a wider range of insurance options to their customers without having to take on the costs and administrative burdens of creating their own insurance products.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Benefits of Including Embedded Insurance in Your Products or Services</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Increased revenue through an additional revenue stream</li>\r\n	<li>Improved customer satisfaction by offering a complete solution</li>\r\n	<li>Competitive advantage over businesses that don&#39;t offer embedded insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Reduced administrative hassle for businesses and customers</li>\r\n	<li>Enhanced Customer Experience</li>\r\n	<li>Enriched Risk Management</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>InstaSure and its customizable embedded insurance product</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>InstaSure is a leading insurance provider that offers embedded insurance solutions to businesses of all sizes. Our customizable insurance product can be tailored to suit the unique needs of any business, whether they provide products or services. With InstaSure, businesses can <strong>unlock new opportunities</strong> and expand their customer base while providing a convenient and <strong>hassle-free insurance experience</strong> to their clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>InstaSure is committed to helping small and large businesses grow and thrive for the long term. Our customizable embedded insurance product allows businesses to provide added value to their customers while protecting their investments. By offering insurance alongside their products or services, they can improve customer satisfaction and loyalty, while also increasing revenue and staying competitive in their respective markets. With InstaSure, businesses can <strong>stay ahead of the game and ensure long-term success.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To sum up, embedded insurance is a simple and effective way for businesses of all sizes to increase revenue and provide value to their customers. By partnering with InstaSure, businesses can customize their insurance offerings to fit their unique products or services and unlock new opportunities for growth. Embedded insurance will provide peace of mind to customers and increase their confidence to purchase from the store again and again. So, the business can potentially gain customer loyalty and generate more revenue in the long run. That&rsquo;s what businesses should do, <strong>think about the long game</strong>, because after all not all businesses can stay in the game till the end, only those who <strong>think about the extended play and plan ahead.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our team is dedicated to helping businesses stay competitive in the market and thrive for the long term. Contact us today to learn more about how we can help you integrate embedded insurance into your business. <strong>Call +880 9606 25252</strong></p>', 'blog', 1, '2023-03-11 14:52:27', '2023-03-11 14:52:27');
