(20, 8, 'Assure 365', '1713755403-6625d50b94ea6.png', 'For 1 year & 1 person by Carnival-Nagad Insurance Company Limited.', 'Hospicash for Accident/Disease/Covid-19 (only Hospitalization) 	BDT 100,000\n\n    Number of insured โ 1\n    Policy validity - 1 year from the date of registration\n    Age: 18 years to 60 Years\n    Any Bangladeshi National\n    Hospicash for Accident/Disease/Covid-19 (only Hospitalization)\n        Tk. 1,000/night (Maximum 20 unique incidents per year)\n        Maximum 5 nights per month\n        RT-PCR test report is required for Covid-19\n        Minimum 24 hours Hospital Stay required for Hospicash', NULL, 364, 650, 650, NULL, NULL, NULL, 50000, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 10000, NULL, NULL, 1000, 5, NULL, NULL, 30, NULL, 'Exclusions:\r\n\r\nThe Following Diseases are excluded from the scope of cover:\r\n\r\n    Cold/Fever/Flu\r\n    Headache/back pain/abdominal pain (unspecified), Pregnancy and HIV related issues\r\n    General Weakness (unspecified)\r\n    Hospitalization due to consuming addictive substance\r\n\r\nCore Exclusions:\r\n\r\n    30 day waiting period from the date of the registration\r\n    Any claim must be raised within 30 days of incident\r\n    Without Doctorโs recommendation, hospital admission will not be considered\r\n    Any congenital infirmity\r\n    Any pre-existing Condition\r\n    Mental, emotional or psychiatric disorders, alcoholism or any other narcotic addiction\r\n    Prophylactic and immunization procedures\r\n    Any procedure which is experimental or not generally accepted by the medical profession (i.e.; acupuncture)\r\n    Any cosmetic or plastic treatment/surgery unless required as reconstructive surgery as a consequence of an injury due to accidents or burns.\r\n    Rest, convalescence or rejuvenation cures, thermal baths or confinement for the purposes of slimming or beautification\r\n    Family planning purposes including termination of pregnancy during the first twelve weeks from the date conception, sterility\r\n    Willful abortion or any complication and/or sequel there from\r\n    Attempted suicide, violation or attempted violation of the law, injuries willfully or intentionally self-inflicted or due to insanity or under the influence of a drug\r\n    Routine examination of eye and ear, fitting or replacement of eyeglasses (including Contract lenses) or hearing aids\r\n    Routine physical examinations (health check-ups), radiotherapy (X-ray, radium or radioactive isotopes treatment), chemotherapy or any form of treatment when not incidental or necessary to the treatment of the injury/illness which caused the hospitalization\r\n    Any types of dental & optical treatment\r\n    Injury arising due to accident while participating in any unlawful activities (e.g. driving a car without a license)\r\n    Non-surgical care for tuberculosis\r\n    Injury or disease directly or indirectly attributed to or civil commotion\r\n    Circumcision\r\n    Injury, destruction or damage caused by nuclear fission, nuclear fusion or irradiation\r\n    AIDS and HIV related diseased\r\n    Treatment or advice by a person or professional not registered under BMDC (Bangladesh Medical & Dental Council)\r\n    Diagnostic tests conducted without recommendation from a MBBS doctor\r\n    Pre-existing (if diagnosed before the enrollment) conditions requiring surgery - for which surgery was done after the enrollment.\r\n    Pre-existing covid-19 not covered\r\n    Other pre-existing cases like problems arising from narcotics abuse, self-harm, or unlawful activities\r\n    Hospice and end of life care\r\n    Maternity related claim will be not cover\r\n    This Waiting Period is also separately applicable for each Family Member(s) of Primary Member. Waiting Period (30 days) for Family Member(s) shall commence from the day of addition of Family Member(s) to the Package\r\n    Health Toiletries (e.g., anti-lice shampoo)\r\n    Drinks (e.g., energy builders)\r\n    Meal for attendant', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '{\"teli_medi_fee_1\":\"50\",\"teli_medi_fee_2\":\"100\",\"teli_medi_fee_3\":\"150\",\"teli_medi_fee_4\":\"200\",\"teli_medi_fee_5\":\"250\",\"teli_medi_fee_6\":\"300\",\"teli_medi_fee_7\":\"350\",\"teli_medi_fee_8\":\"400\",\"teli_medi_fee_9\":\"450\",\"unlimited\":\"500\"}', '50', '100', '150', '200', '250', '300', '350', '400', '450', NULL, 150, 1, 17, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 15, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, '10', '10', 'C', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Green Delta', 100, '{\"provider_name\":\"Green Delta\",\"provider_price\":\"100\",\"provider_coverage_plane\":\"pragati pkg name\",\"provider_coverage_contact\":\"01751212933\",\"provider_coverage_bill_number\":\"5547896\",\"provider_coverage_bill_date\":\"2025-02-07\"}', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-03-31 05:03:05', '2025-02-23 08:25:06'),
(44, 8, 'Number Of Insured: 01 (Individual)', '1717054757-66582d252fe03.png', '<p>25000 Taka Life Coverage, 10,000 Taka Hospital Coverage(IPD), Health Discount Card and 24*7 Insta Doctor Tele Medicine Service.</p>', 'Permanent and Total Disability (PTD) : In case of Permanent and Total Disability resulting from body\r\ninjury directly through any illness or accidental means, which prevents the insured Member from engaging in\r\nany business, occupation or work whatsoever for remuneration or profit and which disability has continued', NULL, 364, 300, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 25000, 25000, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 10000, NULL, 10000, NULL, NULL, 10000, 5, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 9, '[]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 17, NULL, 'nagadMicrosite', NULL, 266, NULL, NULL, 15, NULL, '7', NULL, 'Age Limit: 18-60 years\n\nLife Coverage: Individual Insured can avail this benefit for death due to any reason except exclusions (attached with this mail).\n\nPPD/PTD: Individual Insured can avail Disability benefit as per Schedule except exclusions (attached with this mail).\n\nIPD: Individual Insured can avail Hospitalization benefit except exclusions (attached with this mail).\nFamily Floater Coverage\n\nAge Limit for Primary Member & Spouse: 18-60 years\n\nAge Limit for Children: 3 months to below 18 years\n\nLife Coverage: Primary Member can avail this benefit for death due to any reason except exclusions.\n\nPPD/PTD: Primary Member can avail Disability benefit as per Schedule except exclusions.\n\nIPD: All Family members can avail Hospitalization benefit up to the benefit limit except exclusions.\nCauses of Exclusion for Death Claim\n\na) All pre-existing disease related Death;\nb) Death caused by self-inflicted injury or the commission of or attempted commission of an assault or any unlawful act, or being engaged in any illegal activity or felony;\nc) By participating in illegal activity is not covered;\nd) Suicide while sane or insane;\ne) The condition of Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome (AIDS), or any AIDS related illness or HIV virus.\nExclusions for Hospitalization\n\n    Hospitalization due to any illness or disability or any condition pre-existing or preceding the effective date of coverage commencement.\n    Less than 24 hours of hospitalization.\n    Any maternity treatment related hospitalization.\n    Advice or treatment received from any person other than an MBBS doctor not registered with Bangladesh Medical & Dental Council (BMDC).\n    Hospitalization due to the condition of Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome (AIDS), and HIV (Human Immune Deficiency Virus), or any AIDS related illness or HIV virus.\n    Hospitalization due to any Psychiatric, mental, or nervous disorder.\n    Hospitalization due to exposure of the body, voluntarily or not, to nuclear power or radioactivity in war or warlike operations or in peace.\n    Hospitalization for childbirth, prenatal/postnatal care, or any maternity related conditions.\n    Any Dental and optical treatments.\n    Any congenital infirmity.\n    Hospitalization without a recommendation from a registered physician.\n    Circumcision, prophylactic, and immunization procedures.\n    Mental, emotional, or psychiatric disorders, alcoholism, or any other narcotic addictions.\n    Injury arising due to accident while participating in any unlawful activities, attempted suicide, violation or attempted violation of the law, injuries willfully or intentionally self-inflicted or due to insanity or under the influence of a drug.\n    Obesity, i.e., treatment for, or required as a result of obesity, any cosmetic or plastic treatment/surgery, unless needed as reconstructive surgery as a consequence of an injury due to accidents, or burns.\n    Any experimental or generally unaccepted procedures by medical professionals, i.e., acupuncture, herbal/ayurvedic/homeopathy treatment, alternative medical care (AMC), etc.\n    Non-surgical treatment for tuberculosis, hepatitis B, hepatitis C, and any other vaccinations, all expenses incurred in connection with the donor for any treatment, lupus and other connective tissue and autoimmune disorders, and costs of prostheses, corrective devices.\n    Any treatment for Cancer, radiotherapy, chemotherapy, dialysis.\n    Any treatment provided free by the government.\n    Any charges for food or food supplements (Hotlinks, Viva, Bournvita, etc.), cosmetic creams or oils of any nature, water purifiers, etc. are excluded.\n\nExclusions For Disability Benefit\n\na) Attempted suicide or intentionally self-inflicted injury, while sane or insane.\nb) War, invasion, act of foreign enemy, hostilities (whether war be declared or not), armed or unarmed truce, civil war, mutiny, rebellion, revolution, insurrection, military or usurped power, riots, strike, civil commotion, assault, terrorist act, homicide or any war-like operations.\nc) Service (including peacetime training) in any military, naval, police air force, or similar service, in time of declared or undeclared war or while under orders for war-like operations or restoration of public order.\nd) Making an arrest as an officer of the law.\ne) Committing a felony.\nf) Failure to seek or follow medical advice.\ng) Participation by the insured member in a criminal or unlawful act.\nh) Any injury incurred before the effective date of the cover.\ni) Engaging in or taking part in professional sports or any hazardous pursuits, including but not limited to diving or riding or any kind of race, underwater activities involving the use of breathing apparatus or not, martial arts, hunting, maneuvering, parachuting, bungee-jumping.\nj) Accident occurring while or because the Insured Member is affected by alcohol or any drugs, narcotics or psychotropic substances.\nk) Service, travel, or flight in or descent from any kind of aircraft, except as a passenger in an aircraft operated by a commercial passenger airline on a scheduled air service over an established passenger route.\nl) Nuclear contamination; the radioactive, explosive, or hazardous nature of nuclear fuel materials or property contaminated by nuclear fuel materials or accident arising from such nature.\n\nNote:\n\n    Minimum 24 hours of hospitalization is required to avail of the hospitalization benefit.\n    All types of maternity, Dental, Eye, HIV benefits are excluded.\n    No pre-existing disease is covered.\n    Suicide or Death due to unlawful activity is not covered.\n    If there is PPD/PTD coverage, then the following schedule will be followed during the claim (attached).', 'NID, Doctor Documents , CashMemo ย of all amount', 1, '10', '10', 'C', NULL, NULL, '', 'GreenDelta', 200, NULL, 'LifePkg', NULL, 1, 1, NULL, '2024-05-30 07:39:17', '2024-10-01 06:18:39'),
(45, 8, 'Number Of Insured: 01 (Individual)-Pkg:2', '1717057990-665839c624f00.png', 'Instasure โ Ensuring Peace of Mind for You and Your Loved Ones.', NULL, NULL, 30, 2500, 2500, NULL, NULL, NULL, 100000, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 100000, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 100000, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 50000, NULL, 2000, 5, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 9, '{\"teli_medi_fee_1\":\"50\",\"teli_medi_fee_2\":\"100\",\"teli_medi_fee_3\":\"150\",\"teli_medi_fee_4\":\"200\",\"teli_medi_fee_5\":\"250\",\"teli_medi_fee_6\":\"300\",\"teli_medi_fee_7\":\"350\",\"teli_medi_fee_8\":\"400\",\"teli_medi_fee_9\":\"450\",\"unlimited\":\"500\"}', '50', '100', '150', '200', '250', '300', '350', '400', '450', NULL, NULL, 1, 17, NULL, 'Instasure', NULL, 266, 10, NULL, 15, NULL, '7', '', 'Age Limit: 18-60 years\n\nLife Coverage: Individual Insured can avail this benefit for death due to any reason except exclusions (attached with this mail).\n\nPPD/PTD: Individual Insured can avail Disability benefit as per Schedule except exclusions (attached with this mail).\n\nIPD: Individual Insured can avail Hospitalization benefit except exclusions (attached with this mail).\nFamily Floater Coverage\n\nAge Limit for Primary Member & Spouse: 18-60 years\n\nAge Limit for Children: 3 months to below 18 years\n\nLife Coverage: Primary Member can avail this benefit for death due to any reason except exclusions.\n\nPPD/PTD: Primary Member can avail Disability benefit as per Schedule except exclusions.\n\nIPD: All Family members can avail Hospitalization benefit up to the benefit limit except exclusions.\nCauses of Exclusion for Death Claim\n\na) All pre-existing disease related Death;\nb) Death caused by self-inflicted injury or the commission of or attempted commission of an assault or any unlawful act, or being engaged in any illegal activity or felony;\nc) By participating in illegal activity is not covered;\nd) Suicide while sane or insane;\ne) The condition of Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome (AIDS), or any AIDS related illness or HIV virus.\nExclusions for Hospitalization\n\n    Hospitalization due to any illness or disability or any condition pre-existing or preceding the effective date of coverage commencement.\n    Less than 24 hours of hospitalization.\n    Any maternity treatment related hospitalization.\n    Advice or treatment received from any person other than an MBBS doctor not registered with Bangladesh Medical & Dental Council (BMDC).\n    Hospitalization due to the condition of Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome (AIDS), and HIV (Human Immune Deficiency Virus), or any AIDS related illness or HIV virus.\n    Hospitalization due to any Psychiatric, mental, or nervous disorder.\n    Hospitalization due to exposure of the body, voluntarily or not, to nuclear power or radioactivity in war or warlike operations or in peace.\n    Hospitalization for childbirth, prenatal/postnatal care, or any maternity related conditions.\n    Any Dental and optical treatments.\n    Any congenital infirmity.\n    Hospitalization without a recommendation from a registered physician.\n    Circumcision, prophylactic, and immunization procedures.\n    Mental, emotional, or psychiatric disorders, alcoholism, or any other narcotic addictions.\n    Injury arising due to accident while participating in any unlawful activities, attempted suicide, violation or attempted violation of the law, injuries willfully or intentionally self-inflicted or due to insanity or under the influence of a drug.\n    Obesity, i.e., treatment for, or required as a result of obesity, any cosmetic or plastic treatment/surgery, unless needed as reconstructive surgery as a consequence of an injury due to accidents, or burns.\n    Any experimental or generally unaccepted procedures by medical professionals, i.e., acupuncture, herbal/ayurvedic/homeopathy treatment, alternative medical care (AMC), etc.\n    Non-surgical treatment for tuberculosis, hepatitis B, hepatitis C, and any other vaccinations, all expenses incurred in connection with the donor for any treatment, lupus and other connective tissue and autoimmune disorders, and costs of prostheses, corrective devices.\n    Any treatment for Cancer, radiotherapy, chemotherapy, dialysis.\n    Any treatment provided free by the government.\n    Any charges for food or food supplements (Hotlinks, Viva, Bournvita, etc.), cosmetic creams or oils of any nature, water purifiers, etc. are excluded.\n\nExclusions For Disability Benefit\n\na) Attempted suicide or intentionally self-inflicted injury, while sane or insane.\nb) War, invasion, act of foreign enemy, hostilities (whether war be declared or not), armed or unarmed truce, civil war, mutiny, rebellion, revolution, insurrection, military or usurped power, riots, strike, civil commotion, assault, terrorist act, homicide or any war-like operations.\nc) Service (including peacetime training) in any military, naval, police air force, or similar service, in time of declared or undeclared war or while under orders for war-like operations or restoration of public order.\nd) Making an arrest as an officer of the law.\ne) Committing a felony.\nf) Failure to seek or follow medical advice.\ng) Participation by the insured member in a criminal or unlawful act.\nh) Any injury incurred before the effective date of the cover.\ni) Engaging in or taking part in professional sports or any hazardous pursuits, including but not limited to diving or riding or any kind of race, underwater activities involving the use of breathing apparatus or not, martial arts, hunting, maneuvering, parachuting, bungee-jumping.\nj) Accident occurring while or because the Insured Member is affected by alcohol or any drugs, narcotics or psychotropic substances.\nk) Service, travel, or flight in or descent from any kind of aircraft, except as a passenger in an aircraft operated by a commercial passenger airline on a scheduled air service over an established passenger route.\nl) Nuclear contamination; the radioactive, explosive, or hazardous nature of nuclear fuel materials or property contaminated by nuclear fuel materials or accident arising from such nature.\n\nNote:\n\n    Minimum 24 hours of hospitalization is required to avail of the hospitalization benefit.\n    All types of maternity, Dental, Eye, HIV benefits are excluded.\n    No pre-existing disease is covered.\n    Suicide or Death due to unlawful activity is not covered.\n    If there is PPD/PTD coverage, then the following schedule will be followed during the claim (attached).', 'NID, Doctor Documents , CashMemo  of all amount', 1, '10', '10', 'C', 'on', 2, '[\"Husband\",\"Wife\"]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'HealthPkg', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2024-05-30 08:33:10', '2024-07-31 07:29:53'),
(48, 8, 'Robi Test 1', '1713755403-6625d50b94ea6.png', '<p>25000 Taka Life Coverage, 10,000 Taka Hospital Coverage(IPD), Health Discount Card and 24*7 Insta Doctor Teli Medicine Service.</p>', NULL, NULL, 30, 30, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 25000, 25000, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1000, NULL, 10000, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 9, '[]', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, 'aamarPayMicrosite', NULL, 266, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '\nNatural Death Claim:\n    a. Death Claim form to be filled up and signed by the nominee\n    b. Copy of National ID of the Insured Member.\n    c. Copy of National ID of the nominee\n    d. Copy of the death certificate issued by the authorized person or office such as Union Parishad Chairman, Word Councillar, City Corporation etc.\n    e. If death has occurred in a hospital, copy of the Death Certificate from the Hospital authority.\n Accidental Death Claim:\n    a. Death Claim form to be filled up and signed by the nominee\n    b. Copy of National ID of the Insured Member.\n    c. Copy of National ID of the nominee\n    d. Copy of the death certificate issued by the authorized person or office such as Union Parishad Chairman, Word Councillar, City Corporation etc.\n    e. Copy of Post-mortem Report/Police Report.\n\nMedical Claim:\nIn-Patient treatment: In-Patient treatment bill to be submitted to Pragati Life within 30 (thirty) days from the date of discharge together with supporting documents of the followings:\n    a. Consultant\'s recommendation for hospitalization (photocopy);\n    b. Discharge certificate (photocopy);\n    c. Copy of the patient\'s file while hospitalized (if possible);\n    d. Copy of investigation Reports.\n    e. Money Receipt or Bill of Consultants (Physician/Surgeon) fee; (Original)\n    f. Bill relating to room charges, investigations and other services where applicable\n    g. Bill of medicine/drugs; (Original)\n    h. Bill relating to Surgical Operation charges (operation theatre, surgical team, delivery charge, anesthesia & other charges), where applicable; (Original)\n    i. Bill relating to ancillary charges (e.g. ambulance service, oxygen therapy, blood transfusions etc.) (Original)\n\nCAUSES OF EXCLUSION FOR DEATH CLAIM\n    a. All pre-existing disease related Death;\n    b. Death caused by self-inflicted injury or the commission of or attempted commission of an assault or any unlawful act, or being engaged in any illegal activity or felony;\n    c. By participating in illegal activity is not covered;\n    d. Suicide while sane or insane;\n    e. The condition of Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome (AIDS), or any AIDS related illness or HIV virus.\n\nExclusions for Hospitalization\n    1. Hospitalization due to any illness or disability or any condition pre-existing or preceding the effective date of coverage commencement\n    2. Less than 24 hours of hospitalization;\n    3. Any maternity treatment related hospitalization;\n    4. Advice or treatment received from any person other than a MBBS doctor and not registered with Bangladesh Medical & Dental Council (BMDC);\n    5. Hospitalization due to the condition of Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome (AIDS), and HIV (Human Immune Deficiency Virus), or any AIDS related illness or HIV virus\n    6. Hospitalization due to any Psychiatric, mental or nervous disorder\n    7. Hospitalization due to exposure of the body, voluntarily or not, to nuclear power or radioactivity in war or warlike operations or in peace\n    8. Hospitalization for childbirth, prenatal/postnatal care, or any maternity related conditions\n    9. Any Dental and optical treatments\n    10. Any congenital infirmity\n    11. Hospitalization without a recommendation from a registered physician\n    12. Circumcision, prophylactic, and immunization procedures\n    13. Mental, emotional, or psychiatric disorders, alcoholism, or any other narcotic addictions\n    14. Injury arising due to accident while participating in any unlawful activities, attempted suicide, violation or attempted violation of the law, injuries willfully or intentionally self-inflicted or due to insanity or under the influence of a drug;\n    15. Obesity, i.e., treatment for, or required as a result of obesity, any cosmetic or plastic treatment/surgery, unless needed as reconstructive surgery as a consequence of an injury due to accidents, or burns\n    16. Any experimental or generally unaccepted procedures by medical professionals, i.e., acupuncture, herbal/ayurvedic/homeopathy treatment, alternative medical care (AMC), etc.\n    17. Non-surgical treatment for tuberculosis, hepatitis B, hepatitis C and any other vaccinations, all expenses incurred in connection with the donor for any treatment, lupus and other connective tissue and autoimmune disorders and costs of prostheses, corrective devices,\n    18. Any treatment for Cancer, radiotherapy, chemotherapy, dialysis;\n    19. Any treatment provided free by the government.\n    20. Any charges for food or food supplements (Hotlinks, Viva, Bourn vita etc) cosmetic creams or oils of any nature, water purifiers, etc. are excluded.\n    21. Six months waiting period will be followed in case of hospitalization due to same disease/disability.\n\n', 'NID, Doctor Documents , CashMemo  of all amount', 1, '10', '12', 'B', NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, 100, NULL, 'LifePkg', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, '2024-07-03 06:40:38', '2024-10-23 05:57:23'),
(49, 8, 'Bima.plus combo Gold (with spouse)', '1713755403-6625d50b94ea6.png', '50000 Taka Life Coverage, 30,000 Taka Hospital Coverage(IPD), Health Discount Card and 24*7 Insta Doctor Teli Medicine Service.', NULL, NULL, 364, 3000, 3000, NULL, NULL, NULL, 50000, 50000, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 30000, NULL, 30000, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 9, 'free', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 18, NULL, 'Instasure', NULL, 266, NULL, NULL, 15, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Age Limit: 18-60 years\n\nLife Coverage: Individual Insured can avail this benefit for death due to any reason except exclusions (attached with this mail).\n\nPPD/PTD: Individual Insured can avail Disability benefit as per Schedule except exclusions (attached with this mail).\n\nIPD: Individual Insured can avail Hospitalization benefit except exclusions (attached with this mail).\nFamily Floater Coverage\n\nAge Limit for Primary Member & Spouse: 18-60 years\n\nAge Limit for Children: 3 months to below 18 years\n\nLife Coverage: Primary Member can avail this benefit for death due to any reason except exclusions.\n\nPPD/PTD: Primary Member can avail Disability benefit as per Schedule except exclusions.\n\nIPD: All Family members can avail Hospitalization benefit up to the benefit limit except exclusions.\nCauses of Exclusion for Death Claim\n\na) All pre-existing disease related Death;\nb) Death caused by self-inflicted injury or the commission of or attempted commission of an assault or any unlawful act, or being engaged in any illegal activity or felony;\nc) By participating in illegal activity is not covered;\nd) Suicide while sane or insane;\ne) The condition of Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome (AIDS), or any AIDS related illness or HIV virus.\nExclusions for Hospitalization\n\n    Hospitalization due to any illness or disability or any condition pre-existing or preceding the effective date of coverage commencement.\n    Less than 24 hours of hospitalization.\n    Any maternity treatment related hospitalization.\n    Advice or treatment received from any person other than an MBBS doctor not registered with Bangladesh Medical & Dental Council (BMDC).\n    Hospitalization due to the condition of Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome (AIDS), and HIV (Human Immune Deficiency Virus), or any AIDS related illness or HIV virus.\n    Hospitalization due to any Psychiatric, mental, or nervous disorder.\n    Hospitalization due to exposure of the body, voluntarily or not, to nuclear power or radioactivity in war or warlike operations or in peace.\n    Hospitalization for childbirth, prenatal/postnatal care, or any maternity related conditions.\n    Any Dental and optical treatments.\n    Any congenital infirmity.\n    Hospitalization without a recommendation from a registered physician.\n    Circumcision, prophylactic, and immunization procedures.\n    Mental, emotional, or psychiatric disorders, alcoholism, or any other narcotic addictions.\n    Injury arising due to accident while participating in any unlawful activities, attempted suicide, violation or attempted violation of the law, injuries willfully or intentionally self-inflicted or due to insanity or under the influence of a drug.\n    Obesity, i.e., treatment for, or required as a result of obesity, any cosmetic or plastic treatment/surgery, unless needed as reconstructive surgery as a consequence of an injury due to accidents, or burns.\n    Any experimental or generally unaccepted procedures by medical professionals, i.e., acupuncture, herbal/ayurvedic/homeopathy treatment, alternative medical care (AMC), etc.\n    Non-surgical treatment for tuberculosis, hepatitis B, hepatitis C, and any other vaccinations, all expenses incurred in connection with the donor for any treatment, lupus and other connective tissue and autoimmune disorders, and costs of prostheses, corrective devices.\n    Any treatment for Cancer, radiotherapy, chemotherapy, dialysis.\n    Any treatment provided free by the government.\n    Any charges for food or food supplements (Hotlinks, Viva, Bournvita, etc.), cosmetic creams or oils of any nature, water purifiers, etc. are excluded.\n\nExclusions For Disability Benefit\n\na) Attempted suicide or intentionally self-inflicted injury, while sane or insane.\nb) War, invasion, act of foreign enemy, hostilities (whether war be declared or not), armed or unarmed truce, civil war, mutiny, rebellion, revolution, insurrection, military or usurped power, riots, strike, civil commotion, assault, terrorist act, homicide or any war-like operations.\nc) Service (including peacetime training) in any military, naval, police air force, or similar service, in time of declared or undeclared war or while under orders for war-like operations or restoration of public order.\nd) Making an arrest as an officer of the law.\ne) Committing a felony.\nf) Failure to seek or follow medical advice.\ng) Participation by the insured member in a criminal or unlawful act.\nh) Any injury incurred before the effective date of the cover.\ni) Engaging in or taking part in professional sports or any hazardous pursuits, including but not limited to diving or riding or any kind of race, underwater activities involving the use of breathing apparatus or not, martial arts, hunting, maneuvering, parachuting, bungee-jumping.\nj) Accident occurring while or because the Insured Member is affected by alcohol or any drugs, narcotics or psychotropic substances.\nk) Service, travel, or flight in or descent from any kind of aircraft, except as a passenger in an aircraft operated by a commercial passenger airline on a scheduled air service over an established passenger route.\nl) Nuclear contamination; the radioactive, explosive, or hazardous nature of nuclear fuel materials or property contaminated by nuclear fuel materials or accident arising from such nature.\n\nNote:\n\n    Minimum 24 hours of hospitalization is required to avail of the hospitalization benefit.\n    All types of maternity, Dental, Eye, HIV benefits are excluded.\n    No pre-existing disease is covered.\n    Suicide or Death due to unlawful activity is not covered.\n    If there is PPD/PTD coverage, then the following schedule will be followed during the claim (attached).', 'NID, Doctor Documents , CashMemo of all amount', 1, '12', '10', 'B', 'on', 2, '[\"Owner\",\"Spaouse\"]', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'LifePkg', NULL, 1, 1, NULL, '2024-07-03 06:55:25', '2024-07-09 10:42:15'),
